"Making an effort on their own way" → "In their own way": The correct preposition is "in," not "on."
Original Phrase	Suggested Alternative	Why?
Decent pay job	Well-paying job	More standard adjective usage.
Making an effort	Striving / Working hard	Sounds more active and determined.
On their own way	In their own way	Corrects the preposition error.
She strives to maintain a positive attitude even in difficult times."


